Then
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{u}\|^2 &= (\mathbf{c} \cdot \mathbf{a})^2/\|\mathbf{a}\|^2, \\
\|\mathbf{v}\|^2 &= (\mathbf{c} \cdot \mathbf{b})^2/\|\mathbf{b}\|^2, \\
\|\mathbf{u} \times \mathbf{v}\|^2 &= \|\mathbf{c} \cdot (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b})\|^2/\|\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\|^2,
\end{align*}so
\begin{align*}
\|\mathbf{u}\| &= \|\mathbf{v}\| = \frac{2 \cdot 5/8}{2} = \frac{5}{8}, \\
\|\mathbf{u} \times \mathbf{v}\| &= \|\mathbf{c}\| \cdot \left\| \frac{\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}}{\|\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\|} \right\| \cdot |\cos \theta| = 2 \cdot \left\| \frac{\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}}{\|\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\|} \right\| \cdot \frac{1}{2} = \sqrt{3}.
\end{align*}Therefore, the volume of the parallelepiped generated by $\mathbf{a},$ $\mathbf{b},$ and $\mathbf{c}$ is
\[|\mathbf{u} \cdot (\mathbf{v} \times \mathbf{w})| = |\mathbf{v} \cdot (\mathbf{w} \times \mathbf{u})| = \left| \frac{5}{8} \cdot \frac{5}{8} \cdot \sqrt{3} \right| = \boxed{\frac{25 \sqrt{3}}{64}}.\]

